Navigate the analyses
 01

&lt;h4&gt;Climate Data Processing&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Import, clean and visualise hourly temperature and precipitation records. Compute daily minimum, mean and maximum temperatures, rainfall, and accumulated GDD per sowing season.&lt;/p&gt;


 02

&lt;h4&gt;Leaf Area Model&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fit three-parameter logistic curves to leaf area per plant. Assess goodness of fit (R², AIC), run ANOVA on β₁–β₃, and plot fitted models with first and second derivatives.&lt;/p&gt;


 03

&lt;h4&gt;Plant Height Model&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Same logistic framework applied to plant height. Derivative analysis locates the GDD at maximum elongation rate and acceleration/deceleration thresholds.&lt;/p&gt;


 04

&lt;h4&gt;Leaf Number Model&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Logistic fit to cumulative leaf number per plant. Inflection and critical-point identification to characterise leaf initiation dynamics across sowing dates.&lt;/p&gt;


 05

&lt;h4&gt;Correlation Analysis&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pearson correlation matrix among leaf area, leaf number, and plant height using the full dataset.&lt;/p&gt;

Extract estimated parameters and compute critical points


Show code
# broom::tidy() converts each NLS object into a tidy data frame;
# pivot_wider() places b1, b2, b3 as separate columns.
parameters_ap &lt;-
  mod_ap |&gt;
  mutate(data = map(data, ~.x |&gt; tidy())) |&gt;
  unnest(data) |&gt;
  select(epoca, cultivar, bloco, term, estimate) |&gt;
  pivot_wider(names_from  = term,
              values_from = estimate)

Split data by sowing season


Show code
# Season E1: rows 1–79  (first sowing date)
dftempe1 &lt;-
  dftemp |&gt;
  slice(1:79) |&gt;
  mutate(season = "E1")

# Season E2: rows 79–148 (second sowing date, one row overlap ensures continuity)
dftempe2 &lt;-
  dftemp |&gt;
  slice(79:148) |&gt;
  mutate(season = "E2")

# Combine seasons and compute cumulative GDD within each season
dftemp2 &lt;-
  bind_rows(dftempe1, dftempe2) |&gt;
  relocate(season, .before = data) |&gt;
  group_by(season) |&gt;
  mutate(
    gda  = cumsum(gd),   # Cumulative GDD – method 1
    gda2 = cumsum(gd2)   # Cumulative GDD – method 2
  ) |&gt;
  # Reformat the date for display (DD/MM)
  separate(data, into = c("ano", "mes", "dia")) |&gt;
  unite("data", dia, mes, sep = "/")

dftemp2 |&gt; group_by(season) |&gt; summarise(sum(prec))

